mibdslThreshProfileTable.name: mibdslThreshProfileTable
mibdslThreshProfileTable.description: A list of mibdslThreshProfile profile entries.

mibdslThreshProfileEntry.name: mibdslThreshProfileEntry
mibdslThreshProfileEntry.description: A mibdslThreshProfile entry containing objects that maps to the parameters of mibdslThreshProfile profile.

dslThreshProfile_Name.name: dslThreshProfile_Name
dslThreshProfile_Name.description: The name consists of a null terminated ascii string supplied by the user.

dslThreshProfile_PhysicalAddress_Shelf.name: dslThreshProfile_PhysicalAddress_Shelf
dslThreshProfile_PhysicalAddress_Shelf.description: The number of the shelf that the addressed physical device resides on.

dslThreshProfile_PhysicalAddress_Slot.name: dslThreshProfile_PhysicalAddress_Slot
dslThreshProfile_PhysicalAddress_Slot.description: The number of the slot that the addressed physical device resides on.

dslThreshProfile_PhysicalAddress_ItemNum.name: dslThreshProfile_PhysicalAddress_ItemNumber
dslThreshProfile_PhysicalAddress_ItemNum.description: A number that specifies an addressable entity within the context of shelf and slot.

dslThreshProfile_Enabled.name: dslThreshProfile_Enabled
dslThreshProfile_Enabled.description: TRUE if any trap of this line needs to be monitored.

dslThreshProfile_Atuc15minLofs.name: dslThreshProfile_Atuc15minLofs
dslThreshProfile_Atuc15minLofs.description: The number of Loss of Frame Seconds encountered by a DSL interface within any given 15 min. performance data collection period, which causes the SNMP agent to send a trap. One trap will be sent per interval per interface. A value 0 disables the trap.

dslThreshProfile_Atuc15minLoss.name: dslThreshProfile_Atuc15minLoss
dslThreshProfile_Atuc15minLoss.description: The number of Loss of Signal Seconds encountered by a DSL interface within any given 15 min. performance data collection period, which causes the SNMP agent to send a trap. One trap will be sent per interval per interface. A value 0 disables the trap.

dslThreshProfile_Atuc15minLols.name: dslThreshProfile_Atuc15minLols
dslThreshProfile_Atuc15minLols.description: The number of Loss of Link Seconds encountered by a DSL interface within any given 15 min. performance data collection period, which causes the SNMP agent to send a trap. One trap will be sent per interval per interface. A value 0 disables the trap.

dslThreshProfile_Atuc15minLprs.name: dslThreshProfile_Atuc15minLprs
dslThreshProfile_Atuc15minLprs.description: The number of Loss of Power Seconds encountered by a DSL interface within any given 15 min. performance data collection period, which causes the SNMP agent to send a trap. One trap will be sent per interval per interface. A value 0 disables the trap.

dslThreshProfile_Atuc15minEss.name: dslThreshProfile_Atuc15minEss
dslThreshProfile_Atuc15minEss.description: The number of Errored Seconds encountered by a DSL interface within any given 15 min. performance data collection period, which causes the SNMP agent to send a trap. One trap will be sent per interval per interface. A value 0 disables the trap.

dslThreshProfile_AtucFastRateUp.name: dslThreshProfile_AtucFastRateUp
dslThreshProfile_AtucFastRateUp.description: Applies to Fast channels only. Configured change in rate causing a trap to be sent. A trap is produced when ChanCurrTxRate >= ChanPrevTxRate plus the value of this object. A value 0 disables the trap.

dslThreshProfile_AtucInterleaveRateUp.name: dslThreshProfile_AtucInterleaveRateUp

One trap will be sent per interval per interface. A value 0 disables the trap.
